Drake took to Instagram on June 16 to reveal that his new album, 'Honestly, Nevermind,' would drop at midnight. Some of his famous friends took to the comments section to celebrate the news. "Get your spritzers ready!", DJ Khaled, via Instagram. "It's your time to shine Jimmy Brooks.", Lil Yachty, via Instagram. Drake's last album, 'Certified Lover Boy,' was released in September. 'People' reports it became the most-streamed album on Spotify and Apple Music. This year, Drake collaborated with Kanye West, Future, French Montana and Jack Harlow.